Using this function you can retrieve the height (in cells) of the tile map element. You give the tile map element ID (which you get when you create a tile map element using layer_tilemap_create() or when you use the function layer_tilemap_get_id()), and the function will return the height (number of cells wide).
The unique ID value of the tile map element to get the height of

{ANY_CODE} var lay_id = layer_get_id("espadrilles");
var map_id = layer_tilemap_get_id(lay_id);
var _w = tilemap_get_width(map_id);
var _h = tilemap_get_height(map_id);
total_tiles = (_w * _h);
The above code uses the retrieved tile map ID to get the tile width and height of the tile map and then uses those values to set an instance variable.
